        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test(qa): expand docker lane adapter",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nKeeps step 1 of the real-E2E QA cleanup focused on reusable Docker lane dispatch without leaving unused QA helper modules behind.\n\nThe prior transport-scenario helper from #97915 was only test-consumed, and the script-producer helper added in this PR was not wired to a production QA consumer. The deadcode gate was right to reject that shape.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- Expands `scripts/qa/docker-e2e-lane.ts` with existing Docker E2E lane names needed by upcoming QA scenario wrappers.\n- Adds `--list` and `--help` to the Docker lane adapter so scenario wrappers can discover/validate lane names without duplicating the map.\n- Removes the unused `qa-transport-scenarios` helper and its unit test instead of preserving an unused re-export/helper surface.\n- Removes the broad QA transport helper re-export from `live-transport-scenarios.ts`; live transport code continues to use the existing SDK seam directly.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo taxonomy IDs, product runtime behavior, or QA scenario coverage claims change. This is QA infrastructure cleanup that keeps future script-to-QA migrations grounded in existing executable lanes without adding unused helper APIs.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm deadcode:unused-files`\n- `pnpm deadcode:dependencies`\n- `pnpm deadcode:report:ci:ts-unused`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/shared/live-transport-scenarios.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/extension-test-boundary.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/shared/live-transport-scenarios.ts scripts/qa/docker-e2e-lane.ts`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/qa/docker-e2e-lane.ts --list`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` clean\n",
